{"lemma":"شُرْبَةُ","slug":"شُرْبَةُ","root":"ش.ر.ب","root_slug":"ش-ر-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-ر-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n22033","n22034","n22035","n22036","n22038"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B4%D9%8F%D8%B1%D9%92%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"instance noun of شَرِبَ (šariba)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"dose, portion, swallow of a medicine","examples":[{"text":"وتعجن بدهن اللوز أو الحل، الشربة منه حبة إلى دانقين بسمن بقر أو بدهن الحل.","english":"And knead with almond oil or sesame oil, the dose of it is one pill to two dāniq, with butter or with sesame oil."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"heavy drinker"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"soup"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root ش ر ب (š r b); “to drink”, Phono-semantic matching of Persian شوربا."},"ipa":["/ʃar.ba/","/ʃu.ra.ba/","/ʃur.ba/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n22033","headword_ar":"شَرْبَةٌ","root":"$rb","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A single act of drinking."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A single draught,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quantity that is drunk at once,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of water. (S.) It is said in a prov.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"niEoma miEolaqu Al$~arobapi h`*aA","text_ar":"نِعْمَ مِعْلَقُ الشَّرْبَةِ هٰذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Excellent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"most excellent, is the traveller's drinking-cup,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bowl, that will hold a single draught,"},{"kind":"text","text":"namely,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"this!"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miEolaq","text_ar":"مِعْلَق"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said by As to be a drinking-cup or bowl which the rider upon a camel suspends [to his saddle]: (Meyd:) it is said in describing a camel: (TA:) and it means that, to the place of alighting to which he desires to go, he is content with a single draught, not wanting another: (Meyd, TA:) the prov. is applied to him who, in his affairs, is content with his own opinion, not wanting that of another person. (Meyd.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$arobapu A^abiY Aljahomi","text_ar":"شَرْبَةُ اَبِى الجَهْمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The draught of Abu-l-Jahm"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is said of a thing that is sweet, or pleasant, but in its result unwholesome: (MF, TA:) Abu-l-Jahm was a frequent visiter of the Khaleefeh El-Mansoor El-'Abbásee, who, finding him troublesome, ordered that a poisoned draught should be given to him, in his presence: which having been done, Abu-l-Jahm, pained by the draught, rose to depart; and being asked by the Khaleefeh whither he was going, he answered, Whither thou hast sent me, O Prince of the Faithful. (MF.) ―         -b3-  In the Mo'allakah of Tarafeh, it is applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A draught of wine."},{"kind":"text","text":"(EM p. 87.) ―         -b4-  [In the conventional language of the physicians, it is a term applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A dose of medicine,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as is drunk"},{"kind":"text","text":"and also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as is eaten."},{"kind":"text","text":"]       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A palm-tree that grows from the date stone:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$arabaAtN","text_ar":"شَرَبَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA. [It seems to be there added that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$araAy^ibu","text_ar":"شَرَايِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$araAbiybu","text_ar":"شَرَابِيبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"are also its pls.: the former may be like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaraAy^iru","text_ar":"ضَرَايِرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dar~apN","text_ar":"ضَرَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": the latter is app. a mistranscription, and should perhaps be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$araAy^iybu","text_ar":"شَرَايِيبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$araAy^ibu","text_ar":"شَرَايِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHaAmiyru","text_ar":"مَحَامِيرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHaAmiru","text_ar":"مَحَامِرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", &c.])"}],"source_refs":["Meyd","TA","MF","K"]},{"entry_id":"n22034","headword_ar":"شُرْبَةٌ","root":"$rb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$urobapN mino maA='K","text_ar":"شُرْبَةٌ مِنْ مَا=ءٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quantity of water that satisfies thirst."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$urobapN","text_ar":"شُرْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_i$oraAbN","text_ar":"اـِشْرَابٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[originally an inf. n.] meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A colour tinged over with another colour;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiyhi $urobapN mino HumorapK","text_ar":"فِيهِ شُرْبَةٌ مِنْ حُمْرَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In him is a colour tinged with redness"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, TA:) [and] (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"somewhat of redness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as in the phrase,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiyhi $urobapN","text_ar":"فِيهِ شُرْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In him is somewhat of redness"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (A:) or (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a redness in the face:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whiteness mixed with redness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, TA voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HusobapN","text_ar":"حُسْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":["K","S","TA","A"]},{"entry_id":"n22035","headword_ar":"شَرَبَةٌ","root":"$rb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"act,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"habit, of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"much drinking."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu la*Fw $arabapK","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ لَذًو شَرَبَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he is one who drinks much."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, AHn, TA.)       -A2-  It is also allowable as a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAribN","text_ar":"شَارِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (Msb.)       -A3-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A small trough,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dug,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"around a palm-tree,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"around any other kind of tree, and filled with water,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"holding enough to irrigate it fully,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so that it is plentifully irrigated thereby:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA:) pl. ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$arabN","text_ar":"شَرَبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or rather this is a coll. gen. n., of which the former is the n. un.,] and [the pl. properly so termed is]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$arabaAtN","text_ar":"شَرَبَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kurodu daborapK","text_ar":"كُرْدُ دَبْرَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) which is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masoqaApN","text_ar":"مَسْقَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) [from a comparison of the explanations of all of these words, it seems to mean"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A channel of water for the irrigation of a plot,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tract, of sown land:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, if the explanation"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"msqAp","text_ar":"مسقاة"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the TA, be conjectural, the meaning may be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a portion of such land, having a raised border to retain the water admitted upon it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$arabaAtN","text_ar":"شَرَبَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [coll. gen. n.] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$arabN","text_ar":"شَرَبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as above]. (TA.)       -A4-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thirst."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, T, O, K.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lamo tazalo bihi $arabapN Alyawoma","text_ar":"لَمْ تَزَلْ بِهِ شَرَبَةٌ اليَوْمَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He has not ceased to have thirst to-day."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA='ati","text_ar":"جَا=ءَتِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA_ibilu wabihaA $arabapN","text_ar":"الاـِبِلُ وَبِهَا شَرَبَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The camels came thirsty."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, O.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaEaAmN *uw $arabapK","text_ar":"طَعَامٌ ذُو شَرَبَةٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Food wherewith one has not sufficient water to satisfy thirst."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, TA.) Accord. to the L,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$arabapN","text_ar":"شَرَبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thirst of cattle after the being satisfied with fresh pasture;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because this invites to drink. (TA.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Vehemence of heat."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yawomN *uw $arabapK","text_ar":"يَوْمٌ ذُو شَرَبَةٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A day of vehement heat, in which is drunk more water than at other times."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n22036","headword_ar":"شُرَبَةٌ","root":"$rb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"One"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who drinks much;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, S, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aruwbN","text_ar":"شَرُوبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ar~aAbN","text_ar":"شَرَّابٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) One says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ukalapN $urabapN","text_ar":"اُكَلَةٌ شُرَبَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man who eats and drinks much."},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, S.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n22038","headword_ar":"شَرَبَّةٌ","root":"$rb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", [said to be] the only word of this form except"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jarab~apN","text_ar":"جَرَبَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) [but to this should be added"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bagat~apN","text_ar":"بَغَتَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bagatahu","text_ar":"بَغَتَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A way, mode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner,"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1528},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of being,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"acting"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. (S, O, K.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA zaAla fulaAnN EalaY $arab~apK waAHidapK","text_ar":"مَا زَالَ فُلَانٌ عَلَى شَرَبَّةٍ وَاحِدَةٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one ceased not to be"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"employed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon one affair."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O.)       -A2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A tract of land,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soft,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"plain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"producing herbs, but having in it no trees."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) ―         -b2-  [And] The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"side of a valley."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}